==English==

===Etymology===
From {{He.}} [[יעקב]] ''(Ya‘akov)'', from the Hebrew root [[עקב]] ''(‘akev)'', [[heel]], because Jacob was born just behind Esau, and was grasping Esau’s heel in an effort to prevent him from being born first.

